was playing tricks on me.

233
00:17:04,816 --> 00:17:07,444
Well, thank God someone
believes me anyway.

234
00:17:07,486 --> 00:17:11,114
Unfortunately, my believing you isn't
going to do either one of us any good.

235
00:17:11,156 --> 00:17:14,993
We're going to need some proof
to clear both our names.

236
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:19,873
You think you can get back in there?

237
00:17:20,707 --> 00:17:23,043
Oh, I don't... I don't know.

238
00:17:24,795 --> 00:17:26,463
I mean, if...

239
00:17:31,885 --> 00:17:33,136
No.

240
00:17:33,470 --> 00:17:37,391
- Are you sure? I just need one photo.
- I'm not going back in there.

241
00:17:37,432 --> 00:17:39,476
Alright. Okay.

242
00:17:41,270 --> 00:17:44,314
We're just going to have
find somebody who can.

243
00:17:44,314 --> 00:17:46,066
Hook them up with the
agency that sent you.

244
00:17:46,108 --> 00:17:50,028
No, they only see old money, blue blood
types, it's part of the whole curse thing.

245
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:53,991
We're not going to find any blue bloods
to help us, they don't need the money.

246
00:17:54,032 --> 00:17:57,244
No, but down and out
blue bloods do.

247
00:18:12,551 --> 00:18:14,136
Check.

248
00:18:15,470 --> 00:18:17,014
Bet.

249
00:18:20,601 --> 00:18:22,769
Read 'em and weep,
losers.

250
00:18:22,811 --> 00:18:24,104
Ah. crap!

251
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:32,779
You got a Maxwell Campion
playing here tonight?

252
00:18:32,821 --> 00:18:36,033
That's him there.
Poker table number five.

253
00:18:54,259 --> 00:18:56,345
Hey, pal, wait up.

254
00:18:57,262 --> 00:18:58,430
Do I know you?

255
00:18:58,472 --> 00:19:01,767
No, but I know you.
Did a little research.

256
00:19:01,975 --> 00:19:04,811
And it seems in a few short years
you've managed to gamble away

257
00:19:04,811 --> 00:19:08,857
the fortune your family spent
generations building.

258
00:19:09,483 --> 00:19:12,903
Hey, hear me out.
I'll make it worth your while.

259
00:19:12,945 --> 00:19:15,113
You got the wrong guy.

260
00:19:15,656 --> 00:19:18,450
Five thousand bucks worth your while?

261
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:24,456
We'll need your signature
on the last page.

262
00:19:24,498 --> 00:19:28,252
Just your standard gag.
You don't talk, we don't talk.

263
00:19:29,419 --> 00:19:31,797
Just how ugly is this girl?

264
00:19:32,631 --> 00:19:34,716
I believe the young lady is waiting.

265
00:19:38,887 --> 00:19:41,932
Wow, this guy is
wasting my time.

266
00:19:47,229 --> 00:19:48,897
Oh, he's here.

267
00:19:49,189 --> 00:19:52,943
- Hey, man, look, I'm sorry that I'm late.
- Alright, yeah. Take off the jacket.

268
00:19:55,028 --> 00:19:56,405
Alright.

269
00:19:58,073 --> 00:19:58,782
Hey.

270
00:19:58,782 --> 00:20:00,784
Alright, now... hey you with me?

271
00:20:00,993 --> 00:20:04,872
Alright, the camera is in the lapel.
The rigging is in the sleeve. Put it on.

272
00:20:05,998 --> 00:20:07,249
Come on, it looks great on you.

273
00:20:07,291 --> 00:20:10,794
Now to take a picture
you just raise either arm.

274
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:13,005
Not now.

275
00:20:13,005 --> 00:20:14,339
Alright. Look, I'm sorry, man.

276
00:20:14,548 --> 00:20:17,384
Yeah, I know you are.
Did you have to gamble all night?

277
00:20:17,384 --> 00:20:20,679
Yeah, I still had chips.
I'm good?

278
00:20:20,721 --> 00:20:22,681
Yeah. Let's... come on, let's go.

279
00:20:32,274 --> 00:20:34,234
Don't worry,
I'll get that.

280
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:35,944
And you are?

281
00:20:36,028 --> 00:20:38,614
I'm Max Campion
and the agency sent me.

282
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:42,701
- Oh, right. Campion.
- There you go... shit.

283
00:20:43,243 --> 00:20:44,495
Excuse me?

284
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:47,915
God Damn!

285
00:21:18,779 --> 00:21:21,907
Alright, dear, we've done as you asked.
They're all in the annexe.

286
00:21:21,949 --> 00:21:23,784
All of them?
All of them.

287
00:21:23,826 --> 00:21:27,412
But why you wouldn't rather talk to them
one at a time is beyond me.

288
00:21:27,454 --> 00:21:30,958
I told you mother this way it will be easier
to weed out the unlikelys.

289
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:42,970
Hello, I'm Penelope.
And you must be?

290
00:21:46,098 --> 00:21:48,058
Late for tea?

291
00:21:50,561 --> 00:21:52,062
Jake!

292
00:21:53,605 --> 00:21:56,525
They're out, they're, they're running...
They've all seen her.

293
00:21:56,567 --> 00:21:58,819
Where's Max?

294
00:21:59,027 --> 00:22:00,779
Edward, do you see Max?

295
00:22:00,779 --> 00:22:04,658
I don't see Max. He's not there.
There's no Max.

296
00:22:18,922 --> 00:22:21,008
- How could you?
- Just speeding things up.

297
00:22:21,008 --> 00:22:23,093
Oh, and now you're just going to
make a pig of yourself?

298
00:22:23,135 --> 00:22:25,721
- No, that's already been done for me.
- Stop it.

299
00:22:27,097 --> 00:22:29,600
That was the last of the ho-hos.

300
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,768
Where's your credit card?
I'm going to the store.

301
00:22:31,810 --> 00:22:33,228
No, no, no don't you... hey!

302
00:22:33,353 --> 00:22:35,606
If you want more ho-ho's
I'll send Jake for some.

303
00:22:35,647 --> 00:22:37,733
I'm old enough
to get my own.

304
00:22:37,774 --> 00:22:39,776
Pick me up some cigarettes.

305
00:22:40,194 --> 00:22:42,696
Penelope,
just one man, one man.

306
00:22:42,696 --> 00:22:46,992
And he'll run too. They always run
why can't you accept that?

307
00:22:47,201 --> 00:22:50,454
For seven years I've been
watching them run.

308
00:22:51,455 --> 00:22:55,334
Do you have any idea how that
makes me feel? Do you?

309
00:22:55,375 --> 00:22:58,253
I'm sorry,
but we just can't quit.

310
00:22:58,295 --> 00:22:59,254
Yes we can because...

311
00:22:59,296 --> 00:23:02,257
no matter how much
I want to believe

312
00:23:02,299 --> 00:23:05,219
there's one man who
won't run away

313
00:23:05,260 --> 00:23:06,720
one man who...

314
00:23:12,643 --> 00:23:16,188
Sweet loving angel of all
things merciful.

315
00:23:17,856 --> 00:23:19,399
Did he see?

316
00:23:19,441 --> 00:23:21,360
He must have.
He was there.

317
00:23:21,401 --> 00:23:23,570
- Who is he?
- Who cares? Just go!

318
00:23:23,612 --> 00:23:24,821
- Yes, go.
- No, I can't...

319
00:23:24,863 --> 00:23:26,490
- Go!
- Go!

320
00:23:29,117 --> 00:23:30,786
Damn it.

321
00:23:37,751 --> 00:23:39,753
You're still here?

322
00:23:42,172 --> 00:23:44,424
Did you see?
See?

323
00:23:44,675 --> 00:23:47,052
You didn't see?
I didn't?

324
00:23:47,261 --> 00:23:49,972
Did you?
Did I what?

325
00:23:50,013 --> 00:23:53,433
Don't mess with me.
What? I'm messing with you?

326
00:23:53,433 --> 00:23:55,602
Why are you still here?
Still?

327
00:23:56,770 --> 00:23:58,939
Fine then,
why are you here?

328
00:23:58,981 --> 00:24:01,108
Look I'm sorry. Should I go?

329
00:24:07,281 --> 00:24:11,034
Are you a fan of George Rockham?

330
00:24:12,077 --> 00:24:13,453
Who?

331
00:24:14,997 --> 00:24:17,082
The book you've got in your jacket.

332
00:24:19,459 --> 00:24:21,461
Oh, alright. You caught that, huh?

333
00:24:23,463 --> 00:24:27,384
Well... yeah.
Yeah, it's a great book.

334
00:24:28,635 --> 00:24:30,554
So you've read it?

335
00:24:31,388 --> 00:24:32,514
Well, yeah.

336
00:24:32,556 --> 00:24:35,184
Funny I thought that was the only
surviving copy.

337
00:24:35,225 --> 00:24:41,273
You know what? I meant to read it, but
the library was always out

338
00:24:46,153 --> 00:24:50,157
I saw it was a first edition
and I figured it might be worth something.

339
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,117
So you were stealing it?

340
00:24:53,660 --> 00:24:56,163
Well... Yeah. I was stealing it.

341
00:24:57,748 --> 00:25:00,167
So, you're a fan of the money?

342
00:25:01,168 --> 00:25:05,881
I'm a big fan of the money.
Although, it doesn't much care for me.

343
00:25:05,923 --> 00:25:09,009
Well, maybe you and the money
weren't meant to be.

344
00:25:09,051 --> 00:25:12,137
Hey, I wouldn't go that far.
Jinx me.

345
00:25:14,348 --> 00:25:17,768
There are 326 first editions
in that room.

346
00:25:17,976 --> 00:25:21,605
Of those, 300 are worth
over 50,000.

347
00:25:22,147 --> 00:25:25,484
A dozen or so are worth
over 25,000.

348
00:25:26,026 --> 00:25:29,238
And I'm afraid there's only one
that's valued under a hundred.

349
00:25:29,363 --> 00:25:30,364
Only one, huh?

350
00:25:30,364 --> 00:25:34,785
A little novel, written by a little
nobody, that never amounted to anything.

351
00:25:35,786 --> 00:25:38,539
You don't say. Under a hundred?

352
00:25:39,248 --> 00:25:43,544
I'm afraid so. And...
I'm afraid that it's time for...

353
00:25:43,544 --> 00:25:46,463
- But it's your favourite just the same?
- What?

354
00:25:47,047 --> 00:25:49,132
I said,
'your favourite just the same'.

355
00:25:49,174 --> 00:25:50,509
I heard you.

356
00:25:55,806 --> 00:25:58,809
Top shelf,
third from the left,

357
00:25:58,851 --> 00:26:01,770
'Moby Dick'.
It's a first edition.

358
00:26:03,021 --> 00:26:05,941
But wait till I'm gone
or they'll see you.

359
00:26:06,358 --> 00:26:07,818
See me?

360
00:26:09,486 --> 00:26:10,737
What?

361
00:26:16,076 --> 00:26:17,411
Hello?

362
00:26:19,496 --> 00:26:21,165
<i>Hello?</i>

363
00:26:48,692 --> 00:26:50,027
Got ya!

364
00:26:53,488 --> 00:26:54,948
No?

365
00:27:00,287 --> 00:27:01,705
Penelope?

366
00:27:10,380 --> 00:27:11,715
Penelope?

367
00:27:34,988 --> 00:27:36,865
Will you be back tomorrow?

368
00:27:37,074 --> 00:27:40,327
I knew it.
I knew you were there.

369
00:27:41,245 --> 00:27:42,496
Yeah.

370
00:27:51,755 --> 00:27:54,258
- He'll be back.
- He will.

371
00:27:58,846 --> 00:28:01,890
- So?
- I didn't get it.

372
00:28:02,432 --> 00:28:04,184
How could you not get it,
half the men in this city...

373
00:28:04,226 --> 00:28:06,770
Relax.
I'm coming back tomorrow.

374
00:28:09,815 --> 00:28:10,858
Ow! Door.

375
00:28:11,483 --> 00:28:12,943
You better.

376
00:28:13,694 --> 00:28:15,112
See you tomorrow.

377
00:28:16,905 --> 00:28:18,448
Better.

378
00:28:30,878 --> 00:28:33,297
Sweetheart? What's wrong?

379
00:28:35,132 --> 00:28:38,468
I thought he just knew,
but it says it right here.

380
00:28:40,971 --> 00:28:42,556
Still he chose it.

381
00:28:42,598 --> 00:28:44,850
Of the 2,000 that aren't
your favourite,

382
00:28:44,892 --> 00:28:47,060
he chose the one that is.

383
00:29:35,526 --> 00:29:36,777
Alright. Alright.

384
00:29:57,005 --> 00:29:58,257
<i>Do you play?</i>

385
00:30:01,385 --> 00:30:03,679
I wish you'd stop
doing that.

386
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:05,305
- Do you play?
- The frog?

387
00:30:05,347 --> 00:30:08,809
No, no although I always meant
to pick it up.

388
00:30:08,976 --> 00:30:10,978
But you do play something.

389
00:30:13,272 --> 00:30:16,191
- What makes you say that?
- What do you play?

390
00:30:21,321 --> 00:30:22,739
Guess.

391
00:30:25,492 --> 00:30:27,119
Is this really necessary?

392
00:30:27,161 --> 00:30:29,413
She's finding
his instrument.

393
00:30:29,413 --> 00:30:32,040
Isn't that something a man
should do for himself?

394
00:30:32,166 --> 00:30:33,917
<i>And a one, and a two, and a one.</i>

395
00:30:34,126 --> 00:30:37,880
<i>You are my sunshine,
my only sunshine</i>

396
00:30:38,088 --> 00:30:42,342
<i>You make me happy
when skies are grey.</i>

397
00:30:42,759 --> 00:30:46,221
<i>You'll never know, dear
dear how much I love you.</i>

398
00:30:46,263 --> 00:30:47,556
Are you even playing that?

399
00:30:47,598 --> 00:30:51,101
<i>So please don't take
my sunshine away.</i>

400
00:30:51,143 --> 00:30:53,312
- Okay, it's not the bass.
- No? No?

401
00:30:53,729 --> 00:30:55,564
- Try the drums.
- Alright.

402
00:30:55,606 --> 00:30:57,357
The drums, you play drums.

403
00:30:59,359 --> 00:31:00,611
Okay.

404
00:31:04,281 --> 00:31:09,369
<i>So please don't take...
my sunshine away.</i>

405
00:31:09,578 --> 00:31:12,372
Okay, okay, no, no, no.
No more drums.

406
00:31:12,915 --> 00:31:16,251
No?
Not the drums, it's not the drums...

407
00:31:17,503 --> 00:31:18,462
<i>Alright!</i>

408
00:31:18,462 --> 00:31:20,130
Saxophone, saxophone!

409
00:31:20,547 --> 00:31:21,965
You want sax?

410
00:31:26,887 --> 00:31:30,224
One... two... one, two.

411
00:31:35,646 --> 00:31:39,149
Enough, stop. Stop, stop!

412
00:31:39,191 --> 00:31:42,653
- Enough.
- No? No, alright.

413
00:31:42,736 --> 00:31:44,905
Play the guitar.
The guitar.

414
00:31:45,155 --> 00:31:47,741
Guitar.
It's got to be the guitar.

415
00:31:54,414 --> 00:31:57,334
I don't think that's how
you play the guitar.

416
00:32:13,392 --> 00:32:19,231
Okay, stop, stop. stop!
Please stop, stop.

417
00:32:22,150 --> 00:32:25,195
Oh, my.
That was, that was terrible.

418
00:32:25,279 --> 00:32:26,071
Hey everybody, everybody wave.

419
00:32:26,113 --> 00:32:28,949
Everybody wave to Penelope
and take a bow, alright? And bow.

420
00:32:30,784 --> 00:32:34,121
I know, I know you guys
you were fantastic

421
00:32:34,246 --> 00:32:35,789
though come here.
Thank you so much for everything.

422
00:32:35,831 --> 00:32:37,374
Wait, wait
I'm not done guessing.

423
00:32:37,457 --> 00:32:41,628
Come on, enough about me.
What do you play?

424
00:32:45,215 --> 00:32:48,135
You want to be a hortomacultural what?

425
00:32:48,218 --> 00:32:51,471
A horticulturalist.
You know? Someone who works with plants.

426
00:32:51,638 --> 00:32:52,723
Right.

427
00:32:53,724 --> 00:32:54,850
Why is that funny?

428
00:32:54,892 --> 00:32:59,980
No plants are great. I just thought
of you as like... like a cop.

429
00:33:00,230 --> 00:33:03,150
You know seeing as you've got
the whole interrogation thing down.

430
00:33:03,233 --> 00:33:05,319
Shut up, it's your move.

431
00:33:06,487 --> 00:33:08,030
Alright.

432
00:33:09,281 --> 00:33:12,242
- Oh, you really don't want to do that.
- Why not?

433
00:33:12,284 --> 00:33:15,579
- Because I'll kill her.
- What if I asked you not to?

434
00:33:15,621 --> 00:33:18,874
I'd still kill her.
You'd sort of be begging me to.

435
00:33:19,708 --> 00:33:22,753
So, beer.
You've never had a beer?

436
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,171
I've had a beer.

437
00:33:24,171 --> 00:33:26,256
- On tap?
- No, not on tap.

438
00:33:26,298 --> 00:33:28,342
Well, then you've never had a beer.

439
00:33:28,342 --> 00:33:30,969
- Your knight can't do that.
- My knight?

440
00:33:31,094 --> 00:33:33,180
- The horse.
- Alright.

441
00:33:35,974 --> 00:33:39,311
Hey, how about you and me heading down
to the Cloverdilly pub right now?

442
00:33:39,603 --> 00:33:41,522
Pub Cloverdilly?

443
00:33:41,688 --> 00:33:45,984
Best beer, best blues, some
of the best beer bums in town.

444
00:33:46,026 --> 00:33:48,070
Thanks, maybe later.

445
00:33:51,281 --> 00:33:53,075
Penelope, come on.

446
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:01,542
Come on, you've got to
get out of there sometime.

447
00:34:02,251 --> 00:34:03,377
Right?

448
00:34:05,379 --> 00:34:07,464
What are you waiting for?

449
00:34:26,233 --> 00:34:30,195
You know, truth is, you're...
you're not missing much.

450
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:36,743
Really?
The Cloverdilly pub sounds fun.

451
00:34:36,994 --> 00:34:39,079
Yeah, but... aside from that.

452
00:34:39,913 --> 00:34:44,168
And the street fairs? I hear they sell
really cool stuff right on the street.

453
00:34:44,501 --> 00:34:47,504
You know, the vendors themselves
are pretty cool too.

454
00:34:47,546 --> 00:34:50,007
- Oh, and the park?
- The park is great.

455
00:34:51,675 --> 00:34:53,302
I used to spend
every weekend there

456
00:34:53,343 --> 00:34:56,722
just hanging on a bench
writing stupid love songs...

457
00:34:56,763 --> 00:35:00,100
- People watching.
- Used to? You don't do that anymore?

458
00:35:04,813 --> 00:35:06,690
What are you doing instead?

459
00:35:11,487 --> 00:35:15,449
- Well, beating you at chess.
- I warned you I'd kill her.

460
00:35:15,491 --> 00:35:18,452
That's great because as soon as my guys
here have seen what you've done...

461
00:35:18,494 --> 00:35:20,120
The game will be over,
your queen will be dead.

462
00:35:20,162 --> 00:35:22,456
My king's still pretty active, you know?

463
00:35:22,539 --> 00:35:25,375
Once the queers dead
the kings useless.

464
00:35:26,710 --> 00:35:29,213
- What's that about?
- I don't know?

465
00:35:30,130 --> 00:35:33,717
Maybe he's too depressed to fight.
He really loved her you know?

466
00:35:37,888 --> 00:35:39,431
Yeah, I can see that.

467
00:35:41,850 --> 00:35:44,436
My queen to yours,
checkmate.

468
00:35:44,728 --> 00:35:46,313
You got me.

469
00:36:07,084 --> 00:36:09,670
Man,
what is this guy doing?

470
00:36:10,003 --> 00:36:12,172
Wasting all my film.

471
00:36:12,381 --> 00:36:15,926
He's doing it on purpose.
He's going for the dowry.

472
00:36:15,968 --> 00:36:19,054
I wish I could find a girl
with a dowry.

473
00:36:19,596 --> 00:36:20,889
Give me a break.

474
00:36:20,931 --> 00:36:24,768
Why else would it be taking you so long?
She revealed herself to me straight away.

475
00:36:24,810 --> 00:36:27,604
You know what?
I guess she liked you more.

476
00:36:28,355 --> 00:36:31,775
Why settle for five thousand when
you could get ten times that, right?

477
00:36:31,817 --> 00:36:35,946
Well, maybe you're forgetting -
I've seen her. She is grotesque.

478
00:36:35,988 --> 00:36:36,864
